> In Italian cuisine, ragu is traditionally a succulent meat-based accompaniment to pasta dishes. Though this recipe has the pasta part down, it swaps out meat for protein-packed lentils stewed in a rich, thick and tasty tomato sauce.

Boil a large #pot{} of @salted water{for boiling} for the @Dried Linguine{180%g}.

When boiling, add the linguine to the water and bring back to the boil.

Cook until softened, ~{12%minutes}. Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pot.

Drizzle with @oil{to taste} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

> TIP: If you're in a hurry you can boil the water in your kettle.

Meanwhile, trim the @Carrot{1}, then coarsely grate (no need to peel).

Drain and rinse the @Lentils{1%pack}.

Roughly tear the @Basil{10%g} leaves.

Place a large #pan{} over medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil.

Add the carrot and half the dried @Italian Herbs{1/2%sachet} (double for 4p). Fry until tender, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Stir in the @Chopped Tomato with Onion & Garlic{1%pack}, @Worcester Sauce{1%sachet} and half the torn basil.

Season with @Salt{to taste}, @Pepper{to taste} and @Sugar{1%tsp} then cover and simmer for ~{6-8%minutes}, until slightly reduced.

Add the lentils and half the @Grated Cheese{100%g} and cook for ~{2-3%minutes}. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

Carefully toss the pasta in the sauce.

Dish up hearty helpings of lentil ragu linguine.

Garnish with remaining cheese and torn basil.